 simple task and maintaining it has proven to be extraordinarily challenging.Thomas A. Kochan, Adrienne E. Eaton, Robert B. McKersie, and Paul S. Adler are among a team of researchers who have been tracking the evolution of the partnership between Kaiser Permanente and the Coalition of Kaiser Permanente Unions ever since 2001. They review the history of health care labor relations and present a profile of Kaiser Permanente as it has developed over the years. They then delve into the partnership, discussing its achievements and struggles, including the negotiation of the most innovative collective bargaining agreements in the history of American labor relations. Healing Together concludes with an assessment of the Kaiser partnership's effect on the larger health care system and its implications for labor-management relations in other industries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCollective bargainingxHealth facilitieszUnited States. 0aHealth facilitieszUnited StatesxPersonnel management. 0aHealth services administrationxEmployee participationzUnited States. 0aIndustrial relationszUnited States. 0aLabor-management committeeszUnited States. 0aMedical personnelxLabor unionszUnited States. 4aBusiness (General). 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 4aLabor History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh1 aEaton, Adrienne E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMcKersie, Robert B., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978080145936840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801459368423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780801459368/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press 